race.comment: WAR RIBBON (2) missed the placings behind MAMA JOY in an incredibly tight finish when fresh from a spell last start over 2110m at this track. Not a noted first-up performer so that effort was particularly encouraging. Doesn't need to do much more to be taking this out. CALIFORNIA GRASS (4) raced closer to the speed than usual and it was responsible for her demise last time out at this track. Is a winner here at the trip. Blinkers off and will be ridden cold today - can bounce back without surprising. MAMA JOY (1) added to her fine recent record with a narrow win over 2110m here three weeks back. On trial at the trip but she is lightly raced and showing all the signs of a good stayer. HAPPINESS (3) was eight weeks between runs before his comfortable win over 2000m at Kembla recently. New to this distance but strips fitter and should cope. SCOTTISH PEARL (6) disappointed here last start but is worth another chance with the blinkers applied for the first time.
